	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Zelda 2 &quot;Microchip&quot; shortage was a hoax?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Does anyone remember the reason big N said that Zelda 2 was delayed due to a microchip shortage?
<br />
<br />We all know that Zelda 2 is a MMC1, (SKROM to be exact), which used a 128KB PRG ROM and 128KB CHR ROM.
<br />
<br />MMC1 was pretty common, in most every game at the time. The 128KB mask roms and the CIC were probably also very common, so I don't see any reason this could be delayed due to a chip shortage.
<br />
<br />Maybe Punch-Out which was the only one that used a "MMC2/4" could be delayed to to a shortage.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
