	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's possible that a lot of MMC1 games were being released at the time (rather than an assortment of MMC1 and UNROM/CNROM), and that they didn't have enough of them in stock. Another possible issue is that Zelda 2 also used a battery-backed 8KB RAM chip for storing saved games.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
